                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7388</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-09T14:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mormon colonists about Casas Grandes in danger. With Columbus raid in mind Villa
                    avoided coming north. They are in greater danger his return south. There are
                    from 400 to 500 Mormons in the colonies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
